Hi Stephen, 

Thanks for the good article!

I am just wondering the performance point of view, Is there a any difference between
 Task.Run in the implementation of the method vs Task.Run to call the method ?

```
class MyService
{
  public int CalculateMandelbrot()
  {
    // Tons of work to do in here!
    for (int i = 0; i != 10000000; ++i)
      ;
    return 42;
  }

  public Task<int> CalculateMandelbrotAsync()
  {
    return Task.Run(() => CalculateMandelbrot());
  }
}

```

vs

```
class MyService
